description.0: Spider-Girl takes on the big, bad Kaine! Will she come out on top? Or will she be defeated and disgraced?
description.1: Can the X-Men stop Mikhail before his crazy plan for a new world is achieved?
description.3: Can Rogue withstand the raging fury of Sunfire, when he appears looking for vengeance?
description.5: The Fantastic Four invade San Diego Comic Con!
description.7: From the pages of Avengers Forever, Rick Jones leaps into adventure as Captain Marvel!  Plus, the history of Rick Jones from witnessing the birth of the Incredible Hulk to working alongside Captain America.
description.11: Bounty hunter Aurra Sing has located the Tusken camp where Ki-Adi-Mundi and Sharad Hett have hidden themselves. Now it's time for her boss, Gardulla the Hutt, to turn up the heat and eliminate the Tusken menace forever! This is one issue you won?t want to miss!
description.12: Kir Kanos, the last surviving member of the Emperor's Royal Guard, is the most wanted man in the galaxy. How do you hide when every bounty hunter in every system is on your trail? For Kanos, the answer is to disguise himself as one of the hunters. From Crimson Empire, the untold tale of how Kir Kanos became bounty hunter Kenix Kil!
description.18: Alpha Flight's recuse mission takes a dire turn! And for Wolverine and his team to make it out alive, one Alpha Flight member will have to make the ultimate sacrifice!
description.19: You thought it couldn`t get any worse after Darth Vader told you he was your dad. But now he wants to introduce you to his boss, the evil Emperor Palpatine. Lucky for you, your friends are outside trying to blow up the very Death Star you`re currently standing in...Something tells me you`ve had better days than this. Join Luke, Darth, Han, Leia, and Artoo in the fourth and final volume of Star Wars: The Return of the Jedi --MANGA! The only Star Wars adaptation that can be used as a seat cushion while waiting in line for Episode I!
description.20: Collects Boba Fett: Enemy of the Empire #1-4, Boba Fett #0.5. Before the events of A New Hope, Darth Vader employs Boba Fett, on a mission to discover and bring to Vader a single small box, the contents of which could change the fate of the galaxy. But there's a catch: Vader trusts no one, and the truth of the box's mystery is too important to allow the bounty hunter to live! When Fett retrieves the prize, he finds himself the target of more of Vader's thralls.
description.27: Both are men of destiny. One has been altered forever, transformed into the ultimate warrior by his own government, their "Weapon X" to control and manipulate as they see fit. The one thing they failed to consider is his indomitable will. One has traveled back through time to right the course of a humanity gone horribly wrong. But something has followed him...something full of hate, and intent on destroying him before his mission can be accomplished. They are Wolverine and Cable...and together, they must stand against a being that threatens both the present and future of the planet!
description.29: What does fate have in store for Black Bolt, Medusa, Karnak, Triton, Gorgon, Crystal, Maximus, and Lockjaw?
description.31: Peter Parker starts to lose his grasp on reality, and his own sanity, spiraling into the unknown. We'll give you a hint that Peter himself doesn't know: Chameleon is behind all of this. Buckle your seatbelts.
description.32: T'Challa's homeland is under attack, and the King is surrounded by adversaries. Black Panther stands alone against: the Russian mob, U.S. intelligence, an insane Achebe and worst of all...Captain America! Can T'Challa stay seated on his throne when so many foes want to cast him out?
description.33: It has been determined that the Beyonders' manipulation of Captain America's Shield during Secret Wars has caused a deadly vibranium virus. To end this crisis, Cap with the aid of a computerized manipulator from Tony Stark, travels to Wakanda!
description.34: DEBUT ISSUE! Join Big Brain, The Thing, Human Torch, Ms. Fantastic and Psi-Lord on their first epic adventure fighting The Scientist!
description.35: Spider-Girl, one of Earth's Mightiest Heroes? The Avengers may recruit her after this issue!
description.36: Mikhail has an offer for his brother Colossus - help hi, remake the world again with their sweet Illyana at their side.
description.37: The Avengers are on the ropes and it's up to the Jade Giant to save them!
description.38: In a nightclub in New York City, Rogue runs into Mystique, who has been masquerading as a supermodel for the last few months. Ninjas have been hunting the shapeshifter and she does not know why. When Rogue investigates, she too is attacked.
description.40: Who is Valeria Von Doom? Why is she duking it out with Titania, the Absorbing Man and She-Hulk?! Is she really the daughter of Susan Storm and Victor von Doom like she claims?
description.45: X-Force's recovery mission on Genosha hits a snag when the Master of Magnetism himself, Magneto, turns up to rebuff the team.
description.48: Meet WILD THING - Daughter of WOLVERINE! Rina Logan is eager to follow in her father's footsteps, and she'll get her chance when her blood-hungry rival is kidnapped by an iron suited villain!
description.49: Someone's taking out the survivors of the experiment that gave Peter his powers- including Doc Ock! If the tentacled one has fallen to this mystery villain, can Spidey be far behind? And who's making those mysterious calls to MJ?
description.50: Scarlet Witch Versus Cable! The New Warriors take on the Slingers! Meanwhile, X-Woman Psylocke uncovers a threat emerging from the Brood, as well as the actual grand prize for the Contest (and it's not an appealing prize for any hero)!
description.54: Ki-Adi-Mundi is coming closer to discovering if the mysterious leader of the Tusken Raiders is the legendary Jedi Sharad Hett. Only two things stand in his way: the vicious krayt dragon of Tatooine and the Jedi-killing bounty hunter Aurra Sing! This is one issue you won't want to miss!
description.55: Star Wars Tales'features the world's greatest comics creators and their spins on the'Star Wars'saga, both within and beyond the'continuity!'Mara Jade'meets'Rebel'General'Madine'in'A Night on the Town'by'Timothy Zahnand'Igor Kordey!'A retired Jedi'ignites her'lightsaber'one last time for a battle with'Darth Vader'in'an all-new story'by'Ron Marz'and'1998'Eisner nominee'Claudio Castellini! And super-scribe'Peter David'and penciller Martin Egeland'come together to spin the saga of'Skippy the Jedi Droid! This is'Star Wars'as you've never seen it before!
description.57: Wolverine, Spider-Man, the Thing, Rogue, Thor, Hulk and a legion of heroes are culled from the Avengers, Fantastic Four and the X-Men, and the participants of The Contest begin to wonder: could their alien hosts really have a more sinister agenda?! They better figure it out soon, before they take each other out!
description.62: A blast from Wolverine's past! Logan links up with his old friends at Alpha Flight, to help them on a dangerous rescue mission - Guardian has been kidnapped by A.I.M.!
description.63: Dengar: sly and mercenary. 4-LOM: calculating and precise. Bossk: fierce and unstoppable. All bounty hunters, all deadly, and all after what may be be their greatest prize: a member of the Rebel Alliance and pilot of the Millennium Falcon. But it's not who you think! On the odd planet of Xokhal, the vile Quaffug the Hutt has staged a hunt for his private amusement. With the unscrupulous bounty hunters all vying for the same purse, all rules are thrown out. But Quaffug and his hired rogues may get more than they bargained for from their "helpless" prey.
description.67: The nail-biting conclusion! Revelation is about to crawl from the sewers to daylight, where her death aura will murder thousands! Can Wolverine and Punisher stop her without killing her? And do they even want to? Marvel's bad boys have trashed the other robots that seek to take her out without realizing they've released Failsafe Omega, a construct with a thermonuclear warhead in its guts! Let's see: save the girl, everybody dies. Let Failsafe Omega stop the girl, Manhattan becomes a smoking crater. Tough choice. Marvel's titans of tude get together for four issues of brutality and mayhem. Sounds like a dream book for fans of Wolvie and Frank Castle.
description.72: It's a shocker that strikes at the very origin of Spider-Man as Peter Parker learns that those present at the experiment that gave him his powers are being hunted down, and killed! Meanwhile, Mary Jane's tropical photo shoot is marred by a phone-call from her mysterious stalker.
description.73: The greatest heroes of the Marvel Universe go to war, with each other, in this all-new super slugfest! From deep space comes the Coiterie, a group of intergalactic samaritans who come to Earth seeking its most powerful champion, through all-out combat! But what could possibly make our heroes compete against one another? How about this: the victor receives a miraculous wish of their choice! In other words, the winner could once and for all save mankind!
description.77: Can Black Bolt regain control of his city without going to war?
description.80: A declaration of war has been made between Black Panther and the United States of America! Intelligence agencies pursue T'Challa through the streets of New York City guns blazing. To make it back to Wakanda, Black Panther teams up with the White Wolf! An inside look at the King's beloved.
description.81: Iron Man discovers some very disturbing news about Captain America's shield.
description.82: Spider-Girl finds herself in a duel with the Darkdevil, while Kaine returns to NYC.
description.83: The X-Men's concern grows as they fear he is no longer the man he once was.
description.84: It's the Incredible Hulk vs. Man-Thing in SWAMP FEVER!
description.85: Professor Xavier tells the X-Men to take a hike! While the X-Men disband, Deathbird takes down Bishop. But why?
description.87: There's a new crimelord making moves on the mob, and for hired muscle he's using the hordes of Hades... because he IS Hades! Will the lord of the Underworld now rule our underworld? Standing against him: three intrepid adventurers...and a puppy!'
description.91: Mission to Genosha! X-Force covertly enters the mutant island to recover something at the behest of Peter Wisdom, but it won't be long before they're uncovered! Plus, Sunspot receives a tantalizing offer from a long-time X-Men villain.
description.95: Spider-Girl tangles with a new villain in the SPIDER-GIRL ANNUAL ISSUE! Teenage heart-throb Leonard Groote comes to town and May Parker is there front and center. Groote's former co-star, Melissa Carsdale, crashes the party - with intentions of seeking revenge for having been thrust out of the limelight. IT'S UP TO SPIDER-GIRL TO SAVE THE DAY!
description.96: Sunset unleashes her armament in full, as Iron Man continues to battle War Machine! Will Tony be able to override Jocasta, Baintronics' weaponized AI?
description.97: Only the hardiest beings in the galaxy can withstand the blistering sands of Tatooine for very long, so one can only imagine the fortitude of the nomadic Tusken Raiders who make their home there. But even the toughest among the Sand People, Sharad Hett, may not be able to survive an attack by the dreaded krayt dragon, Tatooine's fiercest predator, unless Jedi Ki-Adi-Mundi offers to help!'
description.98: She moves in silence, chooses her moment, and strikes without mercy. She is Aurra Sing, the most feared bounty hunter that the Republic has ever seen. Aurra has a talent for being in the right place at the right time, and an appetite for those places in the galaxy where chaos reigns and bounties are plentiful... and challenging!

2.text: The rematch of the century: Hulk vs. Wolverine!

4.text: Will Citizen V step in to stop U.S. Agent and the Jury from taking down the T-Bolts? Forced to battle in a high-tech arena to rescue Charcoal, the Thunderbolts are also the last line of defense against a deadly threat to the United States! Does this signal the return of the surprise T-Bolts foe you've been waiting for?! Could be...!

6.text: The return of Scott Summers! Long thought dead in this reality, Cyclops is back as the leader of the Starjammers. But why has he returned to Earth after all this time?

7.text: Rick Jones is not well. After hallucinating and experiencing breaks from reality, he unleashes his shared host, Genis-Vell AKA Captain Marvel, to deal with a monstrous threat that’s taking over the streets.

8.text: Venom crashes Nova's grand finale—and it's personal!

9.text: Special standalone adventure! Blade stands in horror (and total disgust) at the might of White Worm! A creature with regenerative abilities, Blade slices and dices this foe to no avail! And White Worm keeps multiplying…

14.text: THE EIGHTH DAY PROLOGUE Tony Stark visits an archeological dig in Canada, where the Temple of Balthakk has just been unearthed.  But will even Iron Man be able to subdue the one woman force known as Inferno that is unleashed from within?

16.text: Is it the origin of T-Ray, or the origin of Deadpool? Is Deadpool T-Ray? Is T-Ray Wade Wilson? Those questions and more are asked as we glimpse the events that lead to Mercedes Wilson's death from T-Ray's point of view!

17.text: The Avengers take on...the Avengers?  It's a Destiny War as Avengers across time fight each other to the very end.
The Avengers take on...the Avengers?  It's a Destiny War as Avengers across time fight each other to the very end.

18.text: Alpha Flight's recuse mission takes a dire turn! And for Wolverine and his team to make it out alive, one Alpha Flight member will have to make the ultimate sacrifice!

22.text: The team splits up to battle both the Mannites and Death!

23.text: The empty shell of Deathlok continues his rampage across America, and now he’s hitting up Vegas! Will Nick Fury, and an elite task force of S.H.I.E.L.D., be able to leave Deathlok dead in his tracks? Plus, Billy Bailey begins the journey that will reunite his cyborg body to his human mind!

24.text: The Devourer of Worlds has gone mad, and Earth's on his menu! The Silver Surfer and Alicia Masters rocket into space to stop Galactus, only to be attacked by the planet eater's latest and deadliest herald: Red Shift! And even if they can defeat him, will they return in time to save our world from becoming a smoking husk?!

25.text: Witness the birth of the monster as the origin of the Hulk is re-told!

26.text: The manifestations of The Shattering continue as the ragin’ Cajun finds Sabretooth, but not nearly in the shape he expected! What could possibly have done this to Marvel¹s most dangerous mutant, and why is Scalphunter trying to kill them both? The answers all lie with the man known as Sinister, and he'll only talk for a price...a price that could cost the souls of two men, and the lives of those dearest to them!

27.text: Both are men of destiny. One has been altered forever, transformed into the ultimate warrior by his own government, their "Weapon X" to control and manipulate as they see fit. The one thing they failed to consider is his indomitable will. One has traveled back through time to right the course of a humanity gone horribly wrong. But something has followed him...something full of hate, and intent on destroying him before his mission can be accomplished. They are Wolverine and Cable...and together, they must stand against a being that threatens both the present and future of the planet!

28.text: Banner and Thor are betrayed as Ben Grimm is recruited for the war against the Red Skull!

30.text: Last issue Venom returned... could Carnage be far behind?! At last, Peter Parker and Mary Jane finally get to spend a quiet evening at home... until Venom strikes! Kidnapping, J. Jonah Jameson, the fearsome fiend takes the panicked publisher to the scene of Eddie Brock's near suicide. And when the web-slinger comes to the rescue, he winds up flat on his back at Jonah's feet! At long last, will Spidey get unmasked?! Don't ask Venom, he's too busy going to war with Carnage!

39.text: The return of Citizen V! Charcoal has been abducted by the Imperial Forces, the mysterious organization responsible for his creation! In order to get him back, the Thunderbolts must infiltrate their enemy's ranks, but what they find is just the tip of a criminal conspiracy that cuts across the length and breadth of the entire Marvel Universe! Will Citizen V aid the T- Bolts...or betray them?

43.text: Transported back to the 1930s, Shadowcat and Rachel Summers must navigate a world on the brink of a world war!

44.text: The Avengers go to war! The Avengers fight to retake the fallen nation of Slorenia from Ultron, who plans to use Hank Pym's brain patterns to create his "children."

47.text: While Thor remains trapped on Earth, The Enchanters lay siege to an unprotected Asgard â€" and their first target is Odin himself!  But are they worst threat of the day or is another of the Thunder God's enemies pulling the strings?

51.text: This is it! The final issue! And the sinister Sandman is gonna' make certain of it!

52.text: How did Storm become Bloodstorm? And what happened to this world's Kitty Pryde?

56.text: She has haunted Gambit’s every thought and action, threatening to uproot his powers, his personality, and even his personal life. All this...and she isn’t even tangible! True Believers, this is it- the reveal and resolution behind Gambit’s ‘misty green guardian’! Who is Mary Purcell? And why is she so fervently attached to the ragin’ Cajun? Gambit’s going to have to travel through time and space to get this gaseous green lady off his back!

59.text: T-Ray and Deadpool duke it out one last time! But while Deadpool is pre-occupied with fighting, T-Ray shows everybody involved glimpses of Wade and Mercedes's past. So why doesn't Deadpool recognize any of this?

61.text: Humanity across all timelines is threatened!  Who will help an overmatched Avengers team?
Humanity across all timelines is threatened!  Who will help an overmatched Avengers team?

62.text: A blast from Wolverine's past! Logan links up with his old friends at Alpha Flight, to help them on a dangerous rescue mission - Guardian has been kidnapped by A.I.M.!

65.text: Reunited with his paramour, everything is going fine for the Silver Surfer, until the new herald known as Red Shift arrives! The warning has arrived and all must fear his dark arrival! Galactus, the Devourer Of Worlds, is headed towards Earth... and we're on his menu! This intense exploration of the dreaded destroyer of planets blows the lid off the major cosmic questions of the Marvel Universe, such as: What is the secret reason for the existence of Galactus (that was hinted at in FANTASTIC FOUR #262)? Why did Galactus choose a Herald? More specifically, why did he choose Norrin Radd and change him into the Silver Surfer? Why was it vital that the Surfer defied and broke away from his master? Why has everything that has ever happened to the Surfer led to this adventure? And what is the Surfer's ultimate purpose?

66.text: They're back, the two men who have scarred Gambit's life: Sinister and Sabretooth! With the lives of the young Nina and her fellow Mannites hanging in the balance, Remy LeBeau must seek out the help of the man who’s nearly destroyed his life, the man to whom he owes an unimaginable debt: the mad genius known as Sinister! But to get to him, Gambit must go through the psychotic demon that’s tortured his nightmares and stolen the future of countless innocents, the killer called Sabretooth!

67.text: The nail-biting conclusion! Revelation is about to crawl from the sewers to daylight, where her death aura will murder thousands! Can Wolverine and Punisher stop her without killing her? And do they even want to? Marvel's bad boys have trashed the other robots that seek to take her out without realizing they've released Failsafe Omega, a construct with a thermonuclear warhead in its guts! Let's see: save the girl, everybody dies. Let Failsafe Omega stop the girl, Manhattan becomes a smoking crater. Tough choice. Marvel's titans of tude get together for four issues of brutality and mayhem. Sounds like a dream book for fans of Wolvie and Frank Castle.

69.text: SHIELD is attacked by a being simply known as Death! Jean, Cyclops, Wolverine, Archangel, Cable, and X-Man band together to investigate the former Operation Zero Tolerance HQ.

70.text: Weird science meets bio-mechanized warfare in this gritty series starring Marvel’s mighty cyborg! Deathlok, half-man, half-robot, has escaped the inner sanctum of S.H.I.E.L.D. With his consciousness trapped inside six year old Billy Bailey, will Deathlok see the completion of his human form? A new saga for a new Deathlok begins here!

71.text: WAR ERUPTS! The nations of Earth unite behind Dr. Doom, ruler of Europe, to oust the Goblin Queen from power!

74.text: What does it take to kill a spider? Try a Giant-Man!

76.text: What has become of Professor Xavier's dream and how does Scott Summers press on?

78.text: VENOM is BACK and he's haunting Spider-Man more than ever before!

79.text: Ah, the pressures of being a high school senior: applying to colleges…and having a super hero side gig. Not only does Spidey now have to deal with the Sandman's attack on Coney Island, but he also has to escort three dates to prom!

86.text: The explosive final confrontation with Graviton! More intrigue with Jolt at school! The Imperial Forces come looking for Charcoal, the Burning Man! The mystery of the T-Bolts' new HQ deepens! But all of that pales in comparison to our latest shockeroo: Hawkeye and Moonstone? Locking lips? Be here for the startling saga we had to call "Uh Oh...!"

88.text: Shadowcat and Rachel Summers are transported back to the 1930s to confront the man who would become the Shadow King!

89.text: Ultron has slaughtered the people of an entire nation.  As the Avengers plan to retake the besieged country, Ultron captures Wasp, Wonder Man, Vision, and Scarlet Witch; the ones he considers to be his family.

90.text: The daughter of the original Ant-Man and Wasp seeks retribution against the Avengers.

94.text: Jake Olson stands accused!  Handcuffed to his hospital bed, Thor's mortal form faces a challenge from the law. Will The Warriors Three be able to provide the admonishing evidence?

99.text: The Black Widow is dead. Yelena takes up arms against General Khan and gets into more trouble then she bargained for. With little hope, where will Yelena turn to as she squares off against Deathless Frenzy?
